45

46

developed empirical study, with accurate power calculation. However, this is beyond our

47

48

methodological remit here.

49

50

We also would like to highlight that HRV responses are largely individual and, as we shall

51

52

see, this increases the complexity of the study design, suggesting that HRV analysis in ON is more

53

54

reliable when inferences are made at the group level. Toward this end, we refer readers to the related

55

56

empirical works by Brennan et al. (2001) and Melillo et al. (2011), to further appreciate the sensitivity

57

58

of HRV indexes.

59

